item.title: Overgrown trees, 16th June
item.description:
Overgrown trees that are physically touchable from the kitchen window and when we have windy weather constantly hits off the windows. Some residents can’t see through the windows. Some smaller branches are falling off posing a risk to pedestrians and tall trucks/buses hit certain branches at times. In total its all 5 trees that are huge that need some kind of attention. This is an on going issue which has not been resolved and tfl or the council won’t take responsibility for the issue. The trees are outside block 62 and opposite block 62.

Nearest road to the pin placed on the map (automatically generated by OpenStreetMap): 62, Finborough Road, Earl's Court, London

item.title: Tree overgrowing too close to property, 16th June
item.description:
Cherry tree is growing too large and too close to properties no. 41 and 43 Haywood Road. Also causing huge mess on the surrounding ground and into front gardens due to falling trees and in a few weeks, cherries on the ground. Also causing significant amount of bird faeces onto the cars parked under the tree outside property no 41. Can the tree be significantly pruned please to a much smaller size.
